  "prompt": "What could cause your period to be 14 days late other than pregnancy?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why a menstrual period might be 14 days late other than pregnancy. Some of the common factors include:\n\n1. **Stress**: High levels of stress can affect the hormonal balance in the body, potentially delaying menstruation.\n\n2. **Weight Changes**: Significant weight loss or gain can disrupt hormonal balance and affect your menstrual cycle.\n\n3. **Exercise**: Intense physical activity can lead to missed or irregular periods.\n\n4. **Hormonal Imbalances**: Conditions such as polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) or thyroid issues can lead to late or missed periods.\n\n5. **Illness**: Acute or chronic illnesses can impact your cycle.\n\n6. **Medications**: Certain medications, including some types of birth control, can alter your menstrual cycle.\n\n7. **Perimenopause**: As women approach menopause, their cycles can become irregular.\n\n8. **Breastfeeding**: Lactation can delay the return of regular menstrual cycles postpartum.\n\n9. **Travel or Lifestyle Changes**: Alterations in routine or environmental changes can impact your cycle.\n\n10. **Chronic Conditions**: Conditions like diabetes or celiac disease can affect menstrual regularity.\n\nIf a period is significantly late and there is concern, it's a good idea to consult with a healthcare provider to identify any underlying issues.",
